basically my lottery system works as such:

talk to npc to enter lottery for 2m, you can enter up to 5 times 
each entry is added to a fund 
the fund is announced every 15 mins to all players
when the fund reaches 250m a winner is picked and they recieve the 250m
the system uses arraylists to store data and is rather simple to edit :)

NOTE: You will need 602 npc's to use the npc i have used, if you dont have it just change the npc id to an npc you have :)

so first off:

go to Server.java and add the following:
[code]
	public static lottery lottery = new lottery();
[/code]
it should be obvious where it goes lol

next up, again in Server.java add
[code]
				lottery.process();
[/code]
below the other processes such as "objectManager.process();"

now close Server.java and open up ActionHandler.java

under "public void firstClickNpc(int npcType) {" add
[code]
		case 8206:
			if (c.playerRights < 1) {
				c.getDH().sendDialogues(185, 0);
			} else {
				c.sendMessage("Your rank is too high to participate in the lottery!");
			}
		break;
[/code]
this is to tell the server to send the correct dialogues when you click the correct npc

now in clickingButtons.java add
[code]
 else if (c.dialogueAction == 186) {
					Server.lottery.enterLottery(c);
					c.getPA().removeAllWindows();
